com.hunterjdev.mockjdbc

Interface ResultSetProvider

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultResultSetProvider

    public interface ResultSetProvider
    ResultSetProvider is used to encapsulate the logic needed to provide mock ResultSet objects to MockDriver in cases where multiple ResultSet objects are needed by the code under test. Currently, the only type of injection process which can be supported is a predictable sequential operation. Test cases need to be deterministic so that the mock objects can be supplied in the correct sequence.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    James Hunter
